The paper discusses the privacy guarantees of LPWANs, which are wireless networks used for IoT deployments. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the transmission of radio signals and the use of crypto primitives, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between information leakage and communication/computation costs, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG).
